OL,4,CGurkha veterans on hunger strike
OL,5,Coutside Downing Street
OL,6, On Saturday morning, Gyanraj Rai ate
OL,7, his breakfast, headed to Downing
OL,8, Street, and began a protest about his
OL,9, pension. He hasn't eaten since.
OL,11,F"Better to die than be a coward" is a
OL,12,Fmotto of the Nepalese Gurkha soldiers,
OL,13,Fwho have been an integral part of the
OL,14,FBritish Army for more than 200 years.
OL,16,FAnd 63-year-old Mr Rai says he is
OL,17,Fprepared die - to starve to death - if
OL,18,Fthe government does not agree to make
OL,19,Fhis pension equal to the British
OL,20,Fsoldiers he fought alongside for 20
OL,21,Fyears.
